{"id":7249,"date":"2021-09-09T23:00:16","date_gmt":"2021-09-09T23:00:16","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/?page_id=7249"},"modified":"2021-09-10T00:48:12","modified_gmt":"2021-09-10T00:48:12","slug":"wound-management","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wound-management\/","title":{"rendered":"Wound Management"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"7249\" class=\"elementor elementor-7249\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-section-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-237806f elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"237806f\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-24d83c2\" data-id=\"24d83c2\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8178bf5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8178bf5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h1 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Wound Care: Wound Management<\/h1>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3fb9b3c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Basic Principles<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-c991400 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"c991400\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-b748f33\" data-id=\"b748f33\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e878a96 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e878a96\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Debridement<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Definition: Removal of Damaged Tissue or Foreign Objects from a Wound<\/li><li>Devitalized Tissue, Contamination or Foreign Objects Inhibit Wound Healing<ul><li>Stimulates Metalloproteases &amp; Consumes Local Resources Necessary for Healing<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Approaches:<ul><li><em>Surgical<\/em> \u2013 Sharp Excision<ul><li>Preferred for Large Areas or Evidence of Infection<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Irrigation<\/em> \u2013 Generally Use Warm Isotonic Saline in Pulsed-Fashion with Low-Pressure<ul><li>Added Dilute Antiseptics (Iodine, Chlorhexidine, etc) are Unnecessary \u2013 Minimal Antibacterial Action &amp; May Inhibit Wound Healing<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Enzymatic<\/em> \u2013 Application of Exogenous Enzymatic Agents (Collagenase, Papain, etc)<ul><li>Use is Controversial<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Biologic<\/em> \u2013 Maggots Applied to the Wound Bed<ul><li>Secrete Proteolytic Enzymes to Liquify Necrotic Tissue &amp; Ingest, Leaving Healthy Tissue Alone<\/li><li>Can Bridge Between Surgical Debridements or Use When Surgery Not an Option<\/li><li>Primary Disadvantage is the Negative Perception<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Wound Packing<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Using Saline-Soaked Gauze to Pack Dead Space<\/li><li>Adheres to Surrounding Structures as it Dries \u2013 Debrides Necrotic Tissue<ul><li>Also Removes Granulation Tissue<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Should Be Changed 1-3 Times Daily (Before it Becomes Completely Dried)<\/li><li>Should Stop Once All Necrotic Tissue is Removed &amp; Granulation Begins<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Topical Antiseptics<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Can Be Used to Decrease Bacterial Load<\/li><li>Consider for Select Patient Populations<\/li><li>Types:<ul><li><em>Iodine-Based (Povidone Iodine, Cadexomer Iodine\/Iodosorb)<\/em><\/li><li><em>Silver-Based (Foam, Silvercel, Silver Sulfadiazine)<\/em><\/li><li><em>Honey (Medihoney\/Therahoney)<\/em><ul><li>High Osmolarity \u2013 High Sugar &amp; Low Moisture Content<\/li><li>Acidic with Gluconic Acid<\/li><li>High Concentration of Hydrogen Peroxide<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Acetic Acid<\/em><\/li><li><em>Sodium Hypochlorite 0.5% (Dakin\u2019s Solution)<\/em><ul><li>Should Be Diluted to 0.025% (1:20) \u2013 Unnecessarily Cytotoxic at Higher Doses<\/li><li>Generally Used Only for Necrotizing Soft Tissue Infections<\/li><li>Bleach is Sodium Hypochlorite 3-6%<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Antibiotic Therapy<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Indicated for Signs of Local or Systemic Infection<\/li><li>Prophylactic Antibiotics Not Indicated \u2013 Wound Colonization is Normal but Not Necessarily Infected<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-ebe662d elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"ebe662d\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-01a427b\" data-id=\"01a427b\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a671c94 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"a671c94\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Incision Closure<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-4154636 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"4154636\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-93661ba\" data-id=\"93661ba\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-83e39d8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"83e39d8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Incision Closure<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Primary Intention<\/em>: Close Skin Immediately<\/li><li><em>Secondary Intention<\/em>: Close Fascia &amp; Leave Skin Open<ul><li>If Grossly Contaminated<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Tertiary Intention<\/em>: Close Skin After 3-4 Days<ul><li>If Concern for Contamination<\/li><li>Also Known as \u201cDelayed Primary Intention\u201d<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Fascial Closure<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><a href=\"http:\/\/operativereview.com\/fascia-closure\">*See Abdominal Wall: Fascia Closure<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-5fb86c4 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"5fb86c4\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-fcbf15c\" data-id=\"fcbf15c\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-825fe9f elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"825fe9f\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Negative Pressure Wound Therapy (NPWT)<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-200f29e elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"200f29e\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-baa6f00\" data-id=\"baa6f00\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3769b01 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"3769b01\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Basics<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Also Known as Wound Vacuum-Assisted Closure (WVAC)<\/li><li>Uses an Air-Tight Sealed Dressing Under Negative Pressure Over a Wound to Accelerate Wound Healing<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Effects<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Promotes Granulation Tissue<ul><li>Increases Collagen Formation<\/li><li>Increases Inflammatory Cell Migration<\/li><li>Increases Fibroblast Growth Factor (FGF) &amp; Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor (VEGF)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Decreases Edema &amp; Drains Exudate<\/li><li>Draws Wound Edges Together &amp; Bolsters Skin Grafts<\/li><li>Alters Blood Flow \u2013 Positive Pressure Causes Decreased Perfusion Inducing Growth Factor Release<ul><li>*Previously Believed that it Increased Perfusion<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Removes Harmful Corrosive Substances (TNF-\u03b1, Proteases &amp; Matrix Metalloproteinases)<\/li><li>Decreases Bacterial Contamination<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Contraindications<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Exposed Vital Structures (Organs or Blood Vessels\/Vascular Grafts)<\/li><li>Malignancy<\/li><li>Relative Contraindications:<ul><li>Ischemia or Devitalized Tissue<\/li><li>Infection<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Wound Care: Wound Management Basic Principles Debridement Definition: Removal of Damaged Tissue or Foreign Objects from a Wound Devitalized Tissue, Contamination or Foreign Objects Inhibit Wound Healing Stimulates Metalloproteases &amp; Consumes Local Resources Necessary for Healing Approaches: Surgical \u2013 Sharp Excision Preferred for Large Areas or Evidence of Infection Irrigation \u2013 Generally Use Warm Isotonic [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"folder":[36],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/7249"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=7249"}],"version-history":[{"count":4,"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/7249\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":7313,"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/7249\/revisions\/7313"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=7249"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"folder","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/folder?post=7249"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}